        "content": "<p>I'm doing a semi-automated casebash in which I run <code>cases</code> on 4 disjunctions and then apply their results. I need the case-hypotheses named so I can <code>simp</code> using them. This here works:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h11</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h12</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h21</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cases</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h22</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">expose_names</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_2</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_3</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not_lt_of_gt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not_lt_of_gt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not_lt_of_gt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_2</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not_lt_of_gt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h_3</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">order</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but feels brittle because I'm relying on <code>expose_names</code> to produce the specific names <code>h, h_1, h_2, h_3</code>. What is the right way to do this?</p>",
